# Normalise line endings. Without this, editing a file on Windows can rewrite it
# with CRLF (\r\n) line endings, and a stray carriage return is invisible in most
# editors but very much not invisible to the programs that read the file.
#
# This bit us concretely: a CRLF `.env` gave POSTGRES_PASSWORD a trailing \r, so
# the password Postgres stored at init included the \r. Anything reading the same
# CRLF file sent the \r too and matched by accident — but a clean client (the CI
# database, a host-run integration test) sent the password WITHOUT it and got
# "password authentication failed". Forcing LF removes that whole failure class.

# Default: treat everything as text and check it out with LF on every platform.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Files where a stray CR is actively harmful — pin them explicitly.
*.env      text eol=lf
.env.example text eol=lf
*.sh       text eol=lf
*.sql      text eol=lf
Dockerfile text eol=lf
*.mjs      text eol=lf
*.cjs      text eol=lf

# Binary assets must never be line-ending "normalised".
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
